# API / Supabase / share-link rules (for upcoming DemoSection features)

## API integration (Step 1)

- Centralize API calls in `src/lib/` or `src/services/` (create if missing).
- Always implement:
  - timeouts (AbortController)
  - clear error states for UI
  - request de-duplication where appropriate (avoid double-submit)
- Never hardcode secrets in the frontend. Use Vite env vars (`import.meta.env`) for public config only.

## Supabase image matching (Step 2)

- Keep Supabase client initialization in a single module.
- Query only needed fields; paginate/limit results.
- Cache results in memory (per session) for repeated keyword searches.

## Share link without DB (Step 3)

- Keep URLs small:
  - compress/minify payload (short keys, omit defaults)
  - prefer base64url over raw JSON when embedding
- Validate and safely parse URL params. Fail gracefully to defaults.

## html2canvas export (Step 4)

- Render a dedicated export container with stable dimensions.
- Avoid capturing large offscreen DOM trees; capture only the target node.
- Defer heavy work (capture) until user action; show a loading state.

## Exit prevention + SNS share (Step 5)

- Warn only when there is unsaved/unsent user input.
- Use the Web Share API when available; provide a fallback copy-to-clipboard.

